response: A homestudy is a series of meetings with a social worker to provide more information about adoption and help prepare an applicant for parenting an adopted child. You will be asked to pay a fee for your home study of up to several thousand dollars. Agencies may also charge for updates or addendums to your home study, which are required every one to two years. Want to hear more?
